{"analytics_identifier":"OT1243","base_path":"/government/organisations/nhs-counter-fraud-authority","content_id":"72c51156-6779-4d53-bb29-2e878453516f","description":"The NHS Counter Fraud Authority (NHSCFA) is charged with identifying, investigating and preventing fraud and other economic crime within the NHS and the wider health group. Focused entirely on counter fraud work, the NHSCFA is independent from other NHS bodies and directly accountable to the Department of Health and Social Care, carrying out counter fraud functions in respect of the health service in England, on behalf of the Secretary of State. NHSCFA is a special health authority, sponsored by the Department of Health and Social Care .","details":{"acronym":"NHSCFA","alternative_format_contact_email":"","body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>The NHS Counter Fraud Authority (NHSCFA) is charged with identifying, investigating and preventing fraud and other economic crime within the NHS and the wider health group.</p>\n\n<p>Focused entirely on counter fraud work, the NHSCFA is independent from other NHS bodies and directly accountable to the Department of Health and Social Care, carrying out counter fraud functions in respect of the health service in England, on behalf of the Secretary of State.</p>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"NHS Counter Fraud Authority\">NHSCFA</abbr> is a special health authority, sponsored by the <a class=\"brand__color\" href=\"/government/organisations/department-of-health-and-social-care\">Department of Health and Social Care</a>.</p>\n</div>","brand":"department-of-health","foi_exempt":false,"logo":{"crest":"no-identity","formatted_title":"NHS Counter Fraud Authority"},"ordered_corporate_information_pages":[],"ordered_featured_documents":[],"ordered_featured_links":[],"ordered_promotional_features":[],"organisation_featuring_priority":"news","organisation_govuk_status":{"status":"exempt","updated_at":null,"url":"https://cfa.nhs.uk/"},"organisation_political":false,"organisation_type":"spec